HEADWORD: Apocarpous
<hw>Ap`o*car"pous</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>apo-</ets> + Gr.
<grk>karpo`s</grk> fruit.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Either entirely
or partially separate, as the carpels of a compound pistil; -- opposed
to <contr>syncarpous</contr>.</def> <rj><au>Lindley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

